                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/6058: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Commissioner at Riffa</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gade</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-01-05T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 5, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>For your information in connection with Consul Hurley’s No. 15, January 3, 11
                    p.m. United States will not participate in any measures respecting the
                    disposition of Yudenitch’s army.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
